# Project rules

At the start of every task, use these rules:

- **.aidescription** — index of all rules (this file and the list of .cursor/rules/*.mdc)
- **docs/context.txt** — open conversations, restrictions, DB structure, next steps
- **docs/requirements.md** — feature checklist (when implementing features)

Apply in every session:

- **commit-and-devlog.mdc** — before/after every commit (message, devlog in same commit, push)
- **clean-code.mdc** — TDD, atoms, translations, export, minimal change, docs/architecture when needed
- **confirmations.mdc** — before implementing features not in requirements, adding deps, or editing context
- **documentation.mdc** — devlog style, where docs live, when to update frontend-tree and architecture
- **file-management.mdc** — prefer edit over create; no proactive docs
- **communication.mdc** — concise; max 2 questions; track in context
- **code-standards.mdc** — naming, file org, code quality, design, translations
